Joe, a Michigan prisoner housed at the Macomb Correctional Facility where I am also incarcerated, considered contacting prison nurses a month ago.
To their credit, health care staff are working hard to prevent further spread of the highly infectious and deadly virus.
But like Joe, health care staff lack authority to make decisions based on their training and expertise.
Health care, not to be confused with health insurance — in here or out there — is, in fact, a social good.
The solution to the COVID-19 crisis, here inside, is not hope, as that is all incarcerated people at Macomb Correctional Facility are currently working with.